Procedure

1. Open FileZilla, CyberDuck, or WinSCP software on the system.

2. Enter the connection details:

• Host Name / Server IP – Linux VM IP Address

• Username – Linux VM Username

• Password – Linux VM Password

• Port Number – 22

3. Select SFTP (SSH File Transfer Protocol) as the connection type.

4. Click the connect option:

• Quickconnect in FileZilla

• Connect in CyberDuck

• Login in WinSCP

5. After successful connection:

• Left panel displays local system files

• Right panel displays Linux VM files

6. Use drag and drop to upload or download files between the local system and Linux VM.

7. Verify whether the transferred files are available in the destination folder.

8. Close the connection safely after completing the file transfer process.
